rubric.en:
Consider the decision variant (M* = M).

Expected code/algorithm:
nondetSSDDec(A, s, M) {
  foreach (a in A) x[a] = choice(2);
  mStar = 0;
  foreach (a in A) mStar = mStar + x[a] * s[a];
  if (mStar == M) return success;
  else return failure;
}

This is a fully polynomial-time approximation scheme (FPTAS), with relative error bounded by ε.

Expected code/algorithm:
ssdAprox(n, s, M, ε) {
  L[0] = (0);
  for (i = 1; i <= n; ++i) {
    Ltemp = merge(L[i-1], L[i-1] + s[i]);
    trim(Ltemp, ε/n, L[i]);
    remove from L[i] the values larger than M;
  }
  return the largest value in L[n];
}
